Atmosphere is very cool. Our server was professional yet warm. City Mouse follows the covid19 safe practices strictly. The food was very good, especially the appetizers.
Solid location, menu isn’t super unique but done well with friendly service and great ambiance. Recommend!
Quiet spot.  Decent food and drinks, but nothing earth shattering

Great patio, service was wonderful but the food was just so-so. We went for brunch, so maybe dinner menu is better. It'd be a great place to grab drinks and chill out on the patio (if we were still able to do that).
Great food and atmosphere!

TOP 3 Burger in the city. Two delicious crisp beef patties, fresh lettuce and onions, a slightly spicy special sauce, melty cheese and toasted bun make this classic with a twist Burger the best in the city. Great fries and melon hibiscus lemonade. (Loyalist #2, table donkey and stick #3)

It was okay. The menu seemed very limited - not sure if it was due to COVID-19 restrictions or it's the norm of the restaurant. I can say the restaurant was clean and the staff was nice. Cute place but wasn't impressed by the food selection.
It was ok, not a huge selection of apitizers, and you can only be at your table for little over an hour.
Ate brunch here. Really good food!

Great food, cool atmosphere, great service. Definitely a trendy spot (right next to Google building) but it is a little odd that it's in the lobby of a hotel. Not necessarily a bad thing, just odd!  We did 4 plates between two of us, and it was PLENTY of food (we just wanted to try a lot) and all of it was great.

The first time I ate here was for dinner 2 years ago and it was fantastic! I recently came for brunch and was sorely disappointed. I had an everything bagel which was so hard it tore up my mouth. The donut was actually terrible... and it's hard to make a terrible donut, especially in this city.  The patio was nice though.

we enjoyed the fresh air on the patio and chose the roasted chicken, beef tartare, pasta bolognese and skirt steak. every dish was incredible and full of unique flavor combinations. can't wait to come back.
Great service and food. Nice happy hour specials too
good drinks servers a tad rude

Menu is very limited for lunch. I had chopped salad which was supposed to have chickpeas. Not a chickpea in sight. However Brussels sprouts which were a surprise And surprisingly bitter. Also something weirdly crunchy which I think was chia seeds. Not a fan for lunch. Maybe breakfast and happy hour are better. Would not revisit
Do not place a pick up order here. I have waited 30+ minutes for 2 sandwiches after the ready time, it's 9 am in the morning.
Food was great and reasonable price.  Cheeseburger is one of the best in Chicago.

I was really impressed at how spacious and beautiful this place is! But the food was over-priced (West Loop) and there wasn’t anything special or innovative about it. Plus the servers and the host were really rude and the service was very slow. They defenitly weren't very welcoming.. Just overall experience was meh.
Their gas station sandwich haunts my dreams - it was delicious!
love atmosphere, great food
TOO EXPENSIVE.
Great cocktails, great food. The highlight was the squash - I normally like squash, but I've never had squash I would call amazing. This squash was AMAZING.
The food was amazing as was the service.
Had the thanksgiving process fix menu. Decor and service was great. Food a bit over priced.
Avocado toast was wonderful.
This place has a timeless vibe and fantastic service.

The flavor of the sauce on the house-made tagliatelle was deliciously complex. Service was quick and accommodating. I was particularly impressed with the space. It's very large but still feels comfortable. I appreciate being able to have a conversation with my partner without the guests at surrounding tables hearing everything (or vice versa). The bar has tables and couches, giving it a cozy feel- but again, not crowded. I'm looking forward to returning in warm weather to enjoy the outdoor space, equipped with fireplaces. But since it's only November now, I certainly won't wait until spring to return. Tagliatelle calls me back, and soon!
Popped in for a drink. Outdoor ambience is great. A little pricey, but such is life in the West Loop these days.
Outstanding food, was pleasantly surprised!
Was there for breakfast with a colleague. Good food, good service, very accommodating to my health driven food choices.
Awesome!! Need to go back
Excellent place to chill with friends!
Great for a little social gathering. Absolutely love the food here!

Tasty, quiet, spacious, flexable. Stopped in for a lunch with a friend. Lots of seating available (by way of being integrated with w/ hotel). Server was warm and patient as we weren't in a hurry.  Will visit again
Great fresh food and amazing service!

Horrible experience. My boyfriend was planning a surprise marriage proposal and the bar tender completely ruin my night!!! My boyfriend had to leave that place and take me to a more friendly environment to propose to me. Obviously I will never go back!!!!
Overpriced. They're trying too hard.
Family and dog friendly spot, food is good but the cocktails are better

Excellent place for social gathering. The view is great! Parking is a bit hassle as can be related to mega cities. Street parking and garage parking available nearby. It’s one of the best restaurants.
Eh- foods descent, nothing special
Get a seat on the patio. Get their avocado toast. And get a drink. And enjoy their great service, nice ambiance and cool location right in the middle of the tech bustle of Chicago.
Portions are small but everything we had was good with the bolognese and kale salad as the standouts.
Went here for brunch and it was excellent. I reccomend their Bloody Mary's and the breakfast sandwhich
The food was so good and our server Will was on top of game!! We will be coming back soon❤
Delicious! I had the grain bowl and it was so filling. We had a ton of extra food and it was definitely worth the prices!

The food is a total disappointment. Ordered grilled chicken with mushrooms and apricots and got a rotisserie chicken (similar like from a grocery store) with bones!!! Not acceptable!! Ordered mojito, they put no alcohol in my drink. The price they charge you - is not worth it at all! Not recommending.
What a nice surprise.. excellent cosmos...great service...super outdoor seating...super good.
Nice restaurant located in the Ace Hotel

Stopped by City Mouse for a team lunch today. I ordered a Smoked Chicken Salad Sandwich, which our server got wrong. She kept insisting I ordered a smoked salmon dish and was pretty rude when she reluctantly served me the dish I actually ordered. The food was good- filling and well-made, but staff just blatantly  inhospitable.
Steer Clear!

Got a late lunch here on a Thursday afternoon. Ate outside on a nearly empty patio with our 2 dogs. Got the avocado toast, shrimp and corn app and the "quick fix" (pictured) all were very good. Dogs loved the house-made doggy ice cream!  Overall good, dog friendly patio with good food and service!

Super slow service with lack of attention to detail and overall experience for a group of 8 on a slow Wednesday night. We were there for a friend's birthday and every round of drinks, apps, meals was served extremely far apart without any check in from our server or the manager who was standing nearby us all night. The food was fine, but there are plenty of other places within a few blocks radius that have better food and provide a much more enjoyable experience.
Good food. Great ATMOSPHERE
It's ok
The food was really good but the portions were small . When I was there there were not many people around and it was a quite and laid back atmosphere.

Meh. We had a reservation for 8 for brunch. We were seated and received no menus. The server did not notice this until we alerted him while he was trying to take our drink order. Once we placed drink orders, we were not asked nor given cream or sugar for our coffee.  Once we cream and sugar, we realized we didn't have coffee spoons; I used my butter knife. They auctioned our food off ("Who got the avocado toast?") rather than delivering to the correct seat numbers. It is a small menu; we all got some variation of the same things . My food arrived cold. It was difficult to flag down service for condiments/maintenance items. I had the corned beef sandwich; it was okay, not remarkable. The patio was lovely. Maybe no one else in my group noticed these things, but I worked in hospitality for 20 years. As isolated incidents, nothing terrible happened. But collectively, the lack of attention to detail didn't make me feel very welcome and I'm just not likely to return.

Good, American brunch menu with all the classic dishes of the last five years (avocado toast, grain bowl, etc.). Amazing location across from Google- so much street life and art! I’d give them five stars, but they charged us twice for iced tea because we got a refill... seemed a bit cheap on their part considering how much tea bags cost....

We visited during the week on a nice weather day. The server was very busy but very apologetic. The chicken wings are awesome.  The chicken rub  reminds me of Jay's hotstuff chips. The alchol free hibiscus lemonade is so good.

Pretty darn good food with a cute atmosphere. They have mimosas here so it's definitely a good brunch spot or a post hang-over breakfast.  Service was so so, but I think our gal was overwhelmed. I still really enjoyed my burrito and would absolutely go back.  Eat on the patio if you can.
Great small plates. The burger and wings were awesome.
Great burger and fresh cut fries!!  Decent beer selection.
Eclectic food and drinks.
Great patio and craft cocktail selection

Everything was well made and tasty, tried the burratta, pull bread, steak tartar and chocolate cake (shared first 2 with a group of 4), reasonably priced, portions were a bit small but had enough to eat. Went on a Saturday night and it was very loud. Waiters made good suggestions.
Great spot for brunch! One of the only truly dog friendly spaces in Chicago! 🐾

I love City Mouse. I started coming here maybe a few months after it opened because there was so little hype about it. It’s a low-key restaurant / bar flowing off the lobby of the Ace Hotel. The menu is pretty much standard American diner fare, but with an upscale execution. And, when I say upscale, I don’t mean it in a fancy-pants, foie-gras-in-random-foods kind of way. To give you an example, The Breakfast Sandwich is just... good. And, not because of any exotic pricy ingredients. The bread is soft and some sort of pita or naan-like texture with a slight toasting. The sausage and eggs are seemingly unremarkable, but somehow just perfect every time. There’s a hash brown inside that manages to be balanced in being crispy and soft (like how I like it at Waffle Houses). There’s a little of sweet jam to balance the saltiness. The Sandwich: It. Just. Works. Everything from their dinner dishes to their simple oatmeal is just better than what their names suggests. I can’t really explain or replicate it. Plus, the servers are friendly, and there’s a good vibe here. I don’t feel that mild sense of haughtiness from other people relaxing or eating here like I do from say... across the street or elsewhere in West Loop. People bring their dogs, their kids, or whatever else inside. There’s also now a flower shop and a coffee place attached. City Mouse is just a nice little spot. It is getting more popular each time I come. Hope it stays true to it’s beginnings.

Fantastic paced service for our large group. Cocktails tasty and creative. Extensive wine and liquor selection. Impossible to choose from amazing sounding options. Our server was a great guide on plates to share. Shrimp de jonghe and shrimp pasta blew us away as did tempura sweet potatoes. Burger blows your mind. Can't wait to return
Everything was excellent. The food was delicious and the staff were perfect. Highly recommend the tagliatelle. Fish of the day was walleye.
Great drinks 👌

It is a beautiful restaurant.  The food is perfect for sharing and everything we ordered was excellent.  The usual problem in restaurants is the noise level.  Very difficult to have a conversation.  We also had a server who was less than attentive.  We regularly had to chase her down or call on someone else.  It is still worth trying.
Have been for breakfast and dinner, food was delicious both times! Great cocktails and creative menu options. Ambience is poppin at all times!

Located in the lobby of the Ace Hotel, City Mouse is a great dining destination for groups. (Bonus, it's dog friendly.) Don't miss the "Country Mouse" appetizer. At $5 for a single bite, it's not on the cheap side but it's absolutely delicious. Most dishes are perfect for sharing, and pastas in particular are a standout. Do not overlook the desserts -- a dining companion proclaimed a take on St. Louis Gooey Butter Cake to be "the best thing I've ever eaten" (while another dining companion ordered a few more Country Mouse appetizers for dessert -- they are that good). Worth noting that it can get loud at peak times of the evening, so not necessarily the best spot if you're hard of hearing (though outdoor seating is available and they seem to have heat lamps even in cooler months).
Great vibe
Bloody Mary was excellent, the food was good, but the service was bl pt so great.

Despite the tasteful decor the place lacks proper management. The host and waiter were extremely unprofessional. Could not accomodate basic requests. We had to get up and leave. Zero customer service.

This is good restaurant with lots of space and nice furniture. They have chairs with fur on it's back 🙂 The food is good and they make it quite fast. Service is nice, fast, and friendly. Have been there since the midday on Thursday, on the few people have been eating, lots of tables available.
Nice lounge space with filling and delicious breakfast. This area is full of options and this is a nice breakfast spot with a great little shop next door.
Been twice, a year and a half apart. Very hip and swanky vibe, good cocktails, food is fine, not amazing.
Darned good wine list.
The dining service can use help but the bar and food were excellent
Unreal food. The chef(s) killed everything. However if you’re looking for top notch service, turn your eyes elsewhere.

Competitive Pricing with half a portion with questionable quality. UNWORTHY for your $$.  Delicious TAGLIATELLE with nugget looking 1 shrimp. [My 🥇 in Chicago as whole shrimps are usually shown for value of your $$, dish worthiness]  Fishy edge on GRILLED SWORDFISH with 1 clammy shellfish out of 8.  Excellent STUMPTOWN COFFEE CREME BRULEE but you only get half portion for price.  Utensils were appropriately replaced, like a 5-star restaurant.  Yet, my Check flops itself on my table without being asked.  Generally, and Consistently SHADY! 👎👎
Cozy quaint and exotic
Food was great as well as ambiance! Our server, Joy, was fantastic and really took the experience from good to great! Definitely recommend this place!

Great place. Very nice decor and absolutely must try food. We were there for Chicago Restaurant Week. The Special menu offers many choices for everyone. Vegan and Vegetarian. And Carnivores will find specials  as well (short ribs with sweet potato mash). And please ask for Orlando The Server. He made our visit very pleasant. The only thing that was off it was way too loud music

Went in last night with my girlfriend and another friend. We were coming from a black tie event. When my girlfriend asked to order drinks, a tall blonde bartender with glasses immediately said she's not going to serve me without any explanation or even making eye contact. I was not in anyway drunk or out of control, plus dressed very well. If you're looking for a mediocre over priced bar with condescending and honestly kind of racist bartenders, feel free to check this place out. Otherwise there are way better options.

Went with a group of 6 last weekend for restaurant week. Everywhere online the RW price was listed as $36, but we got there and their menu said $48. The manager was rude and insisted that on their social media and website the $48 price was listed. I checked, it was not (maybe they have since added it). Completely unwilling to work with us, would not allow those who still wanted the $48 menu to order it unless we all did. Was a bad experience, I would not go back even though I have heard good things about the food.
It was pretty good
Really cool place, great food, slick atmosphere. Right across from Google office, so lots of techie types hanging out. I had the burger and the turkey chili, both great. Will come again!
The chopped salad was fabulous.  The service was okay and the atmosphere was fun. This restaurant is inside a hotel.
Not a bad spot for an afternoon drink in Fulton Market. Ok service and cocktail menu.

This is at the lobby of the Ace Hotel. It’s a great place to meet people, especially people you may not know very well. It’s well decorated, open and location is easy to find. I had a brunch here that was quite good on the day after Thanksgiving and there was only a handful of people dining there, so I can’t speak for their daily crowd, but the servers were attentive and knowledgeable and food was tasty.
Surprisingly the best food I've had in the West Loop. Better than the other places that get a lot more attention.
The food is good but just good. Being a sister restaurant of giant you expect so much more.
Great place fresh food choices and staff is wonderful and attentive! Love it!
Very good but not filling
Good food and service
Avocado toast was so filling and delicious! Recommend with the egg on top!
A gem! Inventive menu at all times, soothing atmosphere, great service.

They were busy Friday night our server was all over the restaurant. It was the food that didn’t measure up. The venue is geared to group events and parties so maybe I’d give more stars. Otherwise we had a bottle of their West Loop red, which was pretty tasty!
Food was - so - good.
Great place
Great atmosphere and customer service. Also the early start is great for parents.
Spacious, great service
Love sitting by the outdoor fireplace in spring and fall.
Great upscale dog friendly hotel with delicious brunch that aims to please. Definitely stop in with your dog just to grab brunch and a Michelada!

Brunch in October: Now that outdoor seating isn't really an option, things have calmed down in the West Loop, and that includes here at City Mouse. It's much nicer now. This is a bright and open floorplan with communal tables and smaller tables in the dining room, and lower, cushioned seating up front. It's noticeably louder in the dining room, but less conducive to eating in front area.  We started with coconut, banana, chocolate coffee cake. The chocolate is marbled within, the top is a brown suger crumble. It's pretty sweet, but perfect with black coffee. I really did not notice the coconut. Avocado toast was great, though a personal preference would be for toast that isn't so hard and difficult to cut through. The Gas Station breakfast sandwich is like an elite sausage McMuffin  stuffed with perfectly crisp hashbrowns. All that is made just a bit sweet by grape jelly lightly spread on the English muffin. Accompanied by "fancy fruit" - berries, pineapple, no junky melon.  The bottom line is this place has a target audience of hotel guests, nearby office workers, and neighborhood residents, so the modest menu is essentially upscale comfort food. Though it's a bit noisy, it's  modern and comfortable. The staff is casual, young, a bit inexperienced, but making efforts - they have a lot of people on deck so service is fast, plus everyone was helpful.
Great spot for digestifs after a big West Loop dinner.
Delicious! We had a service issue, but once they realized we were waiting they comped the whole bill to make up for it. Excellent service aside from that. Great food.
Very average food (octopus is not at all fresh), friendly customer service but slow, ambiance is very nice though.
Excellent food and drinks, with polite and timely service. Went for business dinner and was very happy.

A beautiful place directly across from the new Google Chicago Headquarters.  The place was beautiful with great outdoor seating.  The food overall was average.  There was nothing that anyone at my table ordered that was unique or blew us away.
Great Japanese wiskey cocktail
Awesome food!!!  Awesome drinks!!!!  Trendy spot with small plates to share.  Try them all!
Hotel restaurant with diverse selection and option for room service. The pasta I ordered was very salty but the noodles were good and the sauce was flavorful.
Great drinks and chicken wings. Lovely atmosphere.
Great food, fantastic outdoor space, reasonable prices.

Class act. My friend and I decided to wait for a table outside, we're told it'll be 30 minutes. An hour and fifteen minutes later, talked with management and they apologized for the miscommunication and we're incredibly accommodating. Outside of the food and drink being amazing, their service showed me they really cared about the customer experience. Really great wait staff.
Very good
Had a great meal here on vacation. Brian the waiter couldn't have been nicer and all of the dishes were great. The burrata with beets and cherry jam was my favorite.
Really great brunch.  Small menu, slightly overpriced
Great furniture.  The old fashioned was excellent.  I think I was sitting on a Saarinen chair.  Google it
Great food. Outdoor seating is nice.
Food was delicious and the cocktails were unique. The atmosphere is also very nice and service was exceptional. Try the Big Shoulders cocktail if you like bourbon.

Great spot with a really nice relaxed atmosphere! The drinks were fun and there was a beer selection that was better than expected. Lots of comfy, trendy areas to sit, drink and eat. But now that it's summer the patio is where to be! There are just as many tables outside as there is inside. Heaters and fire pit for chillier nights. The food was delicious and reasonably priced.
Great place for families and pet lovers! The food is good, love the pink mimosas.
Good coffee and pastry. Limited brunch menu. Very casual

Although people often come here for drinks, the food is what sets this place apartment from other bars in the neighborhood. The roti is very large and was served with amazing dates and roasted eggplant. The pasta dishes we're incredible as well. Would come back for dinner again. Seems like they are not super busy and can accommodate a crowd.

Family friendly, great service, good value. Came here with my 1.5 year old for breakfast, they had a Stokke high chair which was really nice. Food was good, and prices were comparable to other spots in the neighborhood. It was easy to find parking on a nearby street.
Beautiful restaurant with one of the best burgers I've ever had.
Best breakfast burrito in the game.  Fight me.
Good, with a good wine selection, some fun and interesting dishes like the artichoke. Other items, however, are overly salty, and it’s quite loud in the restaurant.
Service needs a lot of help.

Service was outstanding. Our waiter was awesome! The food was very good. We had brunch and everyone loved their dishes. I love that it's family friendly (compared to small fancier Fulton Market places) I brought my infant son with us! The ambience was perfect for a Saturday afternoon. All in all - a really great time with excellent food. My husband and I are very picky with restaurants in Chicago - we have our favorites - but City Mouse was just added to our list! We'll be back to sit outside!

Any place that serves food and allows dogs gets 5 stars. It’s obviously very hard to find an indoor location that allows dogs, so it’s an automatic win. Staff was very friendly to us and our dogs.  Other than the pet friendly aspect, the food was really delicious and the restaurant is beautiful. Gorgeous couches and lighting throughout. I had the smoked chicken salad sandwich. A very unique chicken sandwich and some of the best fries I’ve ever had. Well done!!
Food Was Awesome.. Small Portions So If Your Really Hungry This Isn't The Place For You.. My Drinks Were Refreshing And Staff Was Very Helpful And Friendly
Great place to sit, relax, work, and have incredible food
Chicago's best burger!
Looks like a really cool place that will much more exciting in the summer. Only went for drinks this trip.
Great atmosphere and good food. Can be a little noise.
Dog and human friendly
City Mouse located inside the Ace hotel is a great place to grab breakfast. Located directly across from the Google campus. Has a great staff and possibly the best sour dough toast.
Great food (charred octopus), great drinks (Dark Work), solid service and some soulful background music! It's definitely a place to check out if you're near Fulton Market.
Food was fantastic!! Layout was nice and spacious. Service was perfect. Great new place!!
This place has good food and good service. Went there for brunch. They kept the coffee filled and everyone enjoyed their meal. We'll be back.
Excellent!!!!

Delicious food and wonderful service in a beautiful setting. We went to City Mouse for dinner and had the restaurant week menu, which was four courses for $44. I loved everything I ate and the portions were good sizes. Our entire party enjoyed the food and experience. Cocktails were very good. There was a lovely room behind the row of tables where we were seated, it had a glass wall and drapes that were drawn once a party was seated there, but it looked like a nice setting for a special dinner or occasion. Service between the bar area and the restaurant was seamless, our bar tab was added to the dinner check easily. I will definitely be back.
Great space! Food was very good.

Amazing Restaurant Week Dinner!  Great vibe, very friendly. I love a restaurant where patrons find the dishes so intriguing that cross table chatter is the norm.  Not a single false note. If I had to name favorites, I would pick the octopus, Tagliatelle,  and the chocolate fig cake. I will be back for that dessert alone.  The restaurant is attached to the Ace hotel. Casual set up for the dining room leading to a fairly loud atmosphere. The restaurant is complimented by an amazing outdoor area with fire pits.

The food is good and the waitservice is good, but I was disappointed with 2 things on my last visit. 1) The table next to us inside the restaurant (not out on the patio) had a small dog with them. It was obviously not a service animal because it was poorly behaved and trying to climb on the table. Other friends of the dog owner stopped to visit at that table and they were picking up the dog and playing/petting vigorously in their arms so the dog fur was getting spread around but no one at the restaurant said a word to them. 2) our table was near the door to leave the hotel. A man stood next to our table and lit his cigarette and started smoking it before he went outside.  He stood trying to light it for a while in front of an employee before he succeeded and again nothing was said to stop him.
The chicken salad was a different rendition but delicious nonetheless. I will definitely come back and try other menu items.
Amazing servicing and great food, the pasta dishes are quite similar though so only order one

The ambiance is great especially in the lounge section which features retro decor and furniture. We went to brunch, which is served daily until 3 pm. The frittata was delicious. Service was mediocre. Our server forgot to bring us 2 items that we ordered. When we brought it to her attention, she didn’t rectify the situation... definitely not going back. I don’t recommend this place if you want a nice lace with prompt and attentive service.
Had brunch at City Mouse with my girlfriend. Food was great and the ambience was fantastic. Will definitely come back here again.
Fair food and service in a 'trendy' but empty hotel.  Sure it'll be more popular when the neighborhood catches up.
It was alright. Don't get the broccoli salad
Great place for a quick lunch, not too expensive
We ordered almost everything on the menu and it was all great.  Our server was friendly and the service was quick.
Excellent cocktails and innovative small plates.

My wife's burger was good, and my brussel sprouts cooked perfectly. Cocktails we're quite good, but be prepared to wave your arms a bit for the attention of the millennial wait staff... It wasn't that busy, and the staff was friendly enough, but it was just... odd.
Great food, nice, friendly staff, but a little bit chilly temp inside.

Delicious brunch with a few basics as well as delicious seasonal items. We had the avocado toast (great),  mutsu and farro salad (amazing) and the spinach and goat cheese frittata (solid).  They have great brunch cocktails - try the bloody Mary or the very refreshing Big Three. The only miss was the coffee, which was serviceable, but didn't match the quality of the rest of the menu. Lots of kids here, so it appears family friendly. Very cool outdoor space for the warmer months. We got a reservation, which I would suggest.
5 stars for the Brussels sprouts in the burrata appetizer. Fantastic stuff.
I like this place, food and drinks was good, I like that servers dress like they wants it’s cool. The atmosphere was nice and cozy.
Just average, at least the two things I had.

Came here for a quick bite. Told the server and they were prompt in getting my food and check. Had the burger and fries, burger had some sort of tasty mayo sauce on it. Fries were terrible and meal was a little overpriced, hence the 4 stars.
Hip spot - great food!

Ambiance is good, waitstaff could be a bit more in tune and friendly.  Food was just okay.  For the caliber of chef running this place, I was surprised to find a bowl of mixed-ripeness fruit occupying space on my plate.  .The gas station sandwich has a good amount of potential, but it seems to need a bit of polishing.
The menu is very limited, but the stuff they do have is damn good!
The apps were amazing, across from Google HQ, so it makes for a great meeting place! great views from the rooftop bar!!

OMG!  Chef Pat Shehrin does it again! This place ROCKS! Ciil, hip atmosphere, great service, imaginative cocktails and great food at a good price. Took a friend there for her birthday dinner and she said it was one of the best meals she has had in years!
Went to City Mouse for brunch - such a lovely addition to the neighborhood. Cocktails and food were awesome. Nice wait staff too ;)
